\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. R. petraeum} Wulfen in Jacq., {\i Mise. Austr. Bot.}{\b  2}: 36 (1781) ({\i R. carpaticum }Schultes). Plant 1-3 m. Leaves up to 15 × 15 cm, glabrous or pubescent, sometimes bullate above and glandular beneath. Racemes c. 10 cm, horizontal or drooping, with 20-35 pinkish, campanulate flowers. Sepals ciliate, orbicular-spathulate, the lower part erect, the upper patent; petals ½ as long as the sepals. Upper part of ovary protruding above the disc. Fruit dark purplish-red, acid.{\i  Woods and scrub. Mountains of C. Europe, extending southwards to the Pyrenees, C. Italy and Bulgaria.} Au Bu Cz Ga Ge He Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(W).
