\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. R. sardoum} U. Martelli, {\i Malpighia}{\b  8}: 384 (1894). Plant c. 1 m, without spines. Leaves 10-15 mm wide, ovate to semi-circular, shortly 3-lobed, with numerous subsessile glands; petiole wide, sheathing, glandular-ciliate. Flowers solitary, axillary; pedicels short, bracteoles absent. Sepals greenish-yellow, ovate, deflexed; petals minute. Fruit bright red, glabrous.{\i  Calcareous rocks,} 1000-1200{\i  m. • Sardegna} ({\i near Oliena}). Sa.
