\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. R. alpinum} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 200 (1753) ({\i R. lucidum} Kit.). Plant 1-2 m. Leaves 2-6 cm, usually longer than wide, rather deeply 3-lobed, glabrous or sparsely hairy. Buds up to 10 mm, acute. Dioecious, but with rudimentary organs of the other sex. Flowers in glandular-hispid racemes (longer in male plants), each flower subtended by a conspicuous bracteole 4-8 × 1-2 mm. Flowers small, rotate, greenish; sepals elliptical. Fruit scarlet, glabrous, insipid. 2n = 16. {\i Wood-margins and by mountain streams. N. & C. Europe, extending southwards in the mountains to N. Spain, C. Italy and Bulgaria}. Au Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge He Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs(N, B, C) Su.
